    <div id="progress-bar"></div>

    <div id="deck">
        <!-- Slide 1: Title -->
        <div class="slide active" data-notes="Hi everyone, my name is Waseem Raza, founder of PBuddy. We are building a trusted, peer-to-peer parcel delivery marketplace that allows everyday people to send and receive packages faster and cheaper by utilizing the empty luggage space of people who are already traveling.">
            <h1 class="accent">PBuddy</h1>
            <h2>Peer-to-peer parcel delivery.</h2>
            <p>Faster, cheaper intercity delivery using existing traveler capacity.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Slide 2: Problem -->
        <div class="slide" data-notes="If you want to send a lightweight parcel from London to Manchester today, your options are terrible. Couriers are expensive, and next-day is a massive premium. Meanwhile, thousands travel that exact route with empty space. The capacity is there, but the trust is missing.">
            <h1>Delivery is <span class="accent-red">broken</span>.</h1>
            <div class="grid-3">
                <div class="card">
                    <span class="icon">💸</span>
                    <h3>Too Expensive</h3>
                    <p>Traditional couriers overcharge for lightweight or intercity items.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="card">
                    <span class="icon">🐌</span>
                    <h3>Too Rigid</h3>
                    <p>Same-day / next-day delivery is priced at an extreme premium.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="card">
                    <span class="icon">🧳</span>
                    <h3>Wasted Capacity</h3>
                    <p>Millions travel daily with empty luggage space, but there is no trusted way to use it.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Slide 3: Solution -->
        <div class="slide" data-notes="PBuddy bridges this gap. We connect senders with verified travelers already heading to that destination. Senders get cheaper delivery. Travelers monetize unused space. And most importantly, we provide the verification and escrow systems required to make this safe.">
            <h1>The <span class="accent">trusted</span> marketplace.</h1>
            <div class="grid-3">
                <div class="card">
                    <span class="icon">🔗</span>
                    <h3>Connect</h3>
                    <p>Match senders with verified travelers already taking the route.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="card">
                    <span class="icon">🛡️</span>
                    <h3>Secure</h3>
                    <p>Escrow payments and QR/OTP verification at hand-off.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="card">
                    <span class="icon">💰</span>
                    <h3>Save & Earn</h3>
                    <p>Cheaper delivery for the sender; instant monetization for the traveler.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Slide 4: How It Works -->
        <div class="slide" data-notes="The process is simple. A sender posts a parcel. The platform surfaces verified travelers taking that route. The traveler claims the job, and the sender pays into our escrow. When they meet, a QR scan confirms the hand-off. The same happens at destination.">
            <h1>Simple. Secure. Scalable.</h1>
            <div class="grid-3">
                <div class="card">
                    <span class="icon">📱 1</span>
                    <h3>Post</h3>
                    <p>Sender lists parcel details, destination, and timeline.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="card">
                    <span class="icon">🤝 2</span>
                    <h3>Match</h3>
                    <p>A verified traveler claims the delivery for their existing route.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="card">
                    <span class="icon">✅ 3</span>
                    <h3>Hand-off</h3>
                    <p>Secure QR scan at pickup and drop-off unlocks escrow payment.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Slide 5: Business Model -->
        <div class="slide" data-notes="Our business model is pure marketplace economics. We charge a percentage-based platform fee to the sender, plus a small flat fee for escrow. Because we don't own fleets of vans, and we don't lease warehouses, our margins are excellent and infinitely scalable.">
            <h1>Asset-light. 100% Scalable.</h1>
            <h2>We take a cut of every successful delivery.</h2>
            <p><strong class="accent">Platform Fee:</strong> 10-15% charged to the sender on booking.</p>
            <p><strong class="accent">Trust/Escrow Fee:</strong> Flat fee (£1.50) for secure payment holding.</p>
            <br>
            <p><i>*No fleets. No warehouses. No employed drivers.</i></p>
        </div>

        <!-- Slide 6: Market -->
        <div class="slide" data-notes="The UK domestic parcel delivery market is enormous—over £14 Billion. But we aren't boiling the ocean. We are targeting the specific segment of lightweight, intercity parcels. Our immediate market consists of students, migrant families, and SMEs.">
            <h1>A massive, unoptimized market.</h1>
            <div class="card" style="margin-top:2rem;">
                <h3 class="accent">TAM (£14B+)</h3>
                <p>Total UK domestic parcel delivery market.</p>

                <h3 class="accent" style="margin-top:1.5rem;">SAM (£500M)</h3>
                <p>Intercity, lightweight consumer & SME parcels.</p>

                <h3 class="accent" style="margin-top:1.5rem;">SOM (£25M)</h3>
                <p>Our initial focus: Students, diaspora families, and SMEs on 3 core UK corridors.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Slide 7: Go To Market -->
        <div class="slide" data-notes="Marketplaces fail when they launch everywhere. Like Uber starting only in SF, we are launching exclusively on two to three high-traffic UK city pairs. This guarantees liquidity. Once dominated, we partner with smart lockers to act as Custody Nodes.">
            <h1>Starting with high-density corridors.</h1>
            <div class="grid-3" style="grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;">
                <div class="card">
                    <h3 class="accent">Phase 1: Route Density</h3>
                    <p>Launch exclusively on 2-3 specific, high-traffic UK city pairs (e.g. London ↔ Manchester).</p>
                    <p>Guarantees liquidity: Senders find travelers immediately.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="card">
                    <h3 class="accent">Phase 2: Node Infrastructure</h3>
                    <p>Partner with local corner shops and smart lockers (Custody Nodes).</p>
                    <p>Allows for asynchronous pickup and drop-off.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Slide 8: Competition -->
        <div class="slide" data-notes="Right now, you pay a premium for a traditional courier, which is trusted but expensive. Or you use a Facebook group, which is cheap but unsafe. PBuddy combines the speed and low cost of a peer network with the structured trust of a centralized courier.">
            <h1>Structured trust wins.</h1>
            <div class="matrix">
                <div class="matrix-cell">
                    <h3>Couriers (DPD, RM)</h3>
                    <p>High Cost / Rigid</p>
                </div>
                <div class="matrix-cell winner">
                    <h3 class="accent">PBuddy</h3>
                    <p>Low Cost / Fast & Secure</p>
                </div>
                <div class="matrix-cell">
                    <h3>Standard Post</h3>
                    <p>Low Cost / Very Slow</p>
                </div>
                <div class="matrix-cell">
                    <h3>Facebook / Gumtree</h3>
                    <p>Low Cost / Unsafe</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

