        <div class="slide" data-notes="I’m Waseem, and I am leading the vision and architecture of PBuddy. I have already designed and built the operational flows of our MVP—from the core matching engine to the escrow frameworks.">
            <h1>Built to execute.</h1>
            <div class="card" style="margin-top: 2rem; max-width: 600px;">
                <h3 class="accent">Waseem Raza — Founder</h3>
                <p>Product vision, marketplace design, and logistics workflow architecture.</p>
                <p>Successfully architected the PBuddy MVP, including the escrow and verification trust layers.</p>
                <p>Currently onboarding strategic advisors in logistics and marketplace growth.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Slide 10: The Ask -->
        <div class="slide" data-notes="We are currently raising a £250k pre-seed round. This capital is purely to prove our unit economics. We will use it to complete our MVP, seed our first two UK corridors, and pilot our first custody nodes. Thank you.">
            <h1>Raising £250k Pre-Seed</h1>
            <h2>Objective: Prove unit economics and route liquidity.</h2>
            <div class="card">
                <p><strong class="accent">1. Product:</strong> Complete MVP hardening and smart-locker integrations.</p>
                <p><strong class="accent">2. Growth:</strong> Acquire senders and travelers on our first 2 city-pair corridors.</p>
                <p><strong class="accent">3. Operations:</strong> Launch our first physical 'Custody Node' pilot.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Speaker Notes Panel -->
    <div id="notes-panel">
        <div class="notes-label">Speaker Notes</div>
        <div id="notes-text"></div>
    </div>

    <!-- Navigation Controls -->
    <div id="controls">
        <div>
            <button id="prev-btn" class="nav-btn" onclick="prevSlide()">← Previous</button>
            <button id="next-btn" class="nav-btn" onclick="nextSlide()">Next →</button>
        </div>
        <div>
            <button onclick="toggleNotes()">Toggle Speaker Notes</button>
            <span id="slide-counter" style="margin-left: 20px; color: var(--text-muted);">1 / 10</span>
        </div>
    </div>

    <script>
        /* --- JAVASCRIPT LOGIC --- */
        let currentSlide = 0;
        const slides = document.querySelectorAll('.slide');
        const progressBar = document.getElementById('progress-bar');
        const counter = document.getElementById('slide-counter');
        const prevBtn = document.getElementById('prev-btn');
        const nextBtn = document.getElementById('next-btn');
        const notesPanel = document.getElementById('notes-panel');
        const notesText = document.getElementById('notes-text');

        function updateDeck() {
            // Update active class
            slides.forEach((slide, index) => {
                if (index === currentSlide) {
                    slide.classList.add('active');
                } else {
                    slide.classList.remove('active');
                }
            });

            // Update Progress Bar & Counter
            const progress = ((currentSlide + 1) / slides.length) * 100;
            progressBar.style.width = progress + '%';
            counter.innerText = `${currentSlide + 1} / ${slides.length}`;

            // Update Buttons
            prevBtn.disabled = currentSlide === 0;
            nextBtn.disabled = currentSlide === slides.length - 1;

            // Update Speaker Notes
            notesText.innerText = slides[currentSlide].getAttribute('data-notes');
        }

        function nextSlide() {
            if (currentSlide < slides.length - 1) {
                currentSlide++;
                updateDeck();
            }
        }

        function prevSlide() {
            if (currentSlide > 0) {
                currentSlide--;
                updateDeck();
            }
        }

        function toggleNotes() {
            notesPanel.classList.toggle('visible');
        }

        // Keyboard Navigation
        document.addEventListener('keydown', (e) => {
            if (e.key === 'ArrowRight' || e.key === 'Space') {
                nextSlide();
            } else if (e.key === 'ArrowLeft') {
                prevSlide();
            } else if (e.key === 'n' || e.key === 'N') {
                toggleNotes();
            }
        });

        // Initialize Deck
        updateDeck();
    </script>
</body>
</html>
How to use this:

Copy the code block above.

Open a basic text editor on your computer (like Notepad on Windows or TextEdit on Mac—make sure it's set to plain text).

Paste the code and save the file as pbuddy.html.

Double-click the file to open it in your web browser.

Interactive Features:

Arrow Keys: Use the Left ← and Right → arrows on your keyboard to navigate slides.

Speaker Notes: Click the "Toggle Speaker Notes" button (or press the N key on your keyboard) to bring up Waseem's exact script for each slide, making it perfect for practicing your pitch!

Progress Bar: A teal line at the top of the screen tracks how far through the deck you are.

